  "text": "Other studies have described an increased risk for metabolic and endocrine disease [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , depression [CITATION_3] , cerebral palsy [CITATION_4] , poor cognitive outcome [CITATION_5] , or intellectual disabilities [CITATION_6] in children born from preeclamptic pregnancies compared to non-exposed children. Also, preeclampsia is an independent predictor of low cognitive scores in preterm infants [CITATION_7] .",
